    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <p>
            <alert>Struggling Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Provide pre-made pyramid models with labelled dimensions.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Use pyramids with simple whole-number dimensions for initial practice.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Pair struggling learners with confident problem solvers.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Break down the formula into steps: (1) Find base area, (2) Multiply by height, (3) Divide by 3.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Provide a step-by-step calculation template.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>On-Level Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Complete all practice problems independently.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Explain the difference between a pyramid and a prism to a peer.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Provide mixed practice with different base shapes.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Advanced Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Derive the formula using the relationship with prisms.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Explore real-world applications: Egyptian pyramids, Mayan pyramids, modern architecture.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Apply the concept to composite solids involving pyramids.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Solve optimisation problems: Given a fixed volume, what dimensions minimise the surface area?</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Extension Activity — Egyptian Pyramid Investigation:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            Work in groups.
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol markers="1.">
                <li>
                    <p>Research the dimensions of the Great Pyramid of Giza (base side length approximately <m>230</m> m, original height approximately <m>146.5</m> m).</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Calculate the volume of the Great Pyramid using the pyramid formula.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>If each stone block has a volume of <m>1 \; \text{m}^3</m>, estimate how many stone blocks were used.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Research how long it took to build the pyramid and estimate how many blocks were placed per day.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Compare the volume of the Great Pyramid with modern buildings or structures.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </axiom>

